==English==

===Alternative spellings===
*[[rim shot]]

===Noun===
'''rimshot'''
# A [[percussion|percussive]] note in which the [[drumstick]] hits both the [[drum head|head]] and the [[rim]] of the [[drum]].
# {{colloquial}} A percussive "[[sting]]" or flourish used to punctuate a joke in a cabaret or vaudeville act.

===Usage note===
Technically, the ''sting'' used to punctuate a joke is not a rimshot.  A ''rimshot'' is a particular note (as in sense 1 above); a ''sting'' is a percussive figure consisting of several notes, perhaps a roll followed by a crash cymbal.

